comments.body:
> Isn't no-vertical-alignment the default?

When I was looking at it a week ago, there didn't seem to be *any* valign configuration that I could find.  Doesn't mean it wasn't there, I just couldn't find it.  :-)  That was what led me to assume that it was simply always on.

> This is configurable. Enable bin-packing for arguments and/or parameters.

Sort of.  It doesn't seem to have the style that I really want.  For example:

```scala
// formals
def foo(abc: Int, deff: Int, efg: Int) = {
  stuff
}

// assuming the above MUST be line broken
def foo(
    abc: Int,
    deff: Int,
    efg: Int) = {

  stuff
}

// actuals
foo(abc, deff, efg)

foo(
  abc,
  deff,
  efg)
```

Note that the fact that the formals are aligned with the method name is coincidental (obviously forced by the fact that `def` is a three-character keyword).  I just want the double-indent.

I don't believe there is a way to achieve the above (again, assuming the lines *must* be broken; if not forced, I prefer leaving the lines alone).  Obviously, this isn't the style that everyone desires, which is why I think it should be configurable.  :-)
